  "decision_conditions": [
    "The development represents inappropriate development in the green belt to which no very exceptional circumstances exist. The development therefore conflicts with Policy DMEI 4 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Part 2 - Development Management Policies (2020), Policy G2 of the London Plan (2021) and Paragraphs 152 and 153 of the National Planning Policy Framework (2023)",
    "The proposed six lighting columns due to their excessive height in this location results in significant visual intrusion and a highly conspicuous form of development that results in significant harm to the character and visual amenity of the area. The development therefore conflicts with Policy D3 of the London Plan (2021), Policy BE1 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Part One Strategic Policies (2012) and Policy DMHB 11 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Part 2 - Development Management Policies (2020).",
    "The lighting would result in a significant level of harm to the amenities and quality of life of surrounding residents by reason of light pollution, light spillage and glare. The development therefore conflicts with Policy DMHB 11 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Part 2 - Development Management Policies (2020), Policy D3 of the London Plan (2021) and Paragraph 191 of the National Planning Policy Framework (2023)."
